Program: Discovery
Title: Matters Of The Heart - part three
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jry6m
Last Broadcast Date: 02 October 2002
The issue of organ donation, can mechanical hearts replace real ones? Biological bypass: demand exceeds supply in organ donation and mechanical hearts have limited success. Rebuilding hearts by engineering new muscle could finally stem the tide of fatal heart disease. Presenter: Geoff Watts.